replyContent: Sorry to hear of this problem. In fact the app's calculations are very accurate. The weak link in the chain is the accuracy of the device's compass. You can almost always improve accuracy by performing a calibration. Please see in-app help and FAQs for instructions.

content: This app works on the basic premise that it establishes the position of north magnetic field and from this point, determines the sun's arc at a particular date/time. The fact that it fails in getting the basics right renders it completely useless. A colleague and I both used this app on a recent project on our respective devices and neither paid-for version could provide even near-accurate results. Literally a waste of money. If the developers are reading this submission, I'd like a refund, please.
replyContent: Sorry to hear of these problems. In fact the app's calculations are very accurate. The weak link in the chain is the accuracy of the device's compass. You can almost always improve accuracy by performing a calibration. Please see in-app help and FAQs for instructions.

replyContent: Hi Ludovic - please try the latest update - just finished a huge overhaul with many new and improved features and fixes. Note that compass calibration is something that is part of the OS, not any app. Best advice is to rotate your device slowly 360degs around at least two different exes. After that you should get much improved accuracy.
